//dbpedia.org/resource/International_Space_Station\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Space Station\", \"types\": [\"Q25956\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Space_Station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Space_Station\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 392, \"to\": 409}, {\"ngram\": \"theParisOlympics\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 430}, {\"ngram\": \"a new sport\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 462}, {\"ngram\": \"mosaics\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"a mystery artist\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 522}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Invader\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 549}, {\"ngram\": \"acrossFrance\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 585}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 606}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vincent Giraud, one of the artist's Parisian fans, is already an avid player.\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 672, \"end\": 679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.2099553861214006e-13, \"text\": \"Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the artist's Parisian fans\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"an avid player\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He downloaded Invader's addictive \\\"Flash Invaders\\\" mobile-phone game that awards points to users who find and photograph the colorful and quirky pieces of pixelated art.\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 919, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Invader's addictive \\\"Flash Invaders\\\" mobile-phone game\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"awards\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 830}, {\"ngram\": \"users\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"the colorful and quirky pieces\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"pixelated art\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 918}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quickly hooked, Giraud has in just a year already tracked down 1,565 of them, accumulating so many points that he has rocketed into the leaderboard's top 1,000, out of more than 360,000 players.\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 1115, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Giraud\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 943}, {\"ngram\": \"just a year\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 962}, {\"ngram\": \"so many points\", \"from\": 1012, \"to\": 1026}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 360,000 players\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1114}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In a few months I found and flashed all those in Paris,\\\" says Giraud, game-name Vince-Vader.\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7174758504898245e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a few months\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1133}, {\"ngram\": \"Giraud\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1186}, {\"ngram\": \"game-name Vince-Vader\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1209}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hunting for Invader mosaics, looking up and around for them on walls, pavements, bridges and even atop theEiffel Tower, is \\\"another way of discovering the city.\\\"\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1372, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Invader mosaics\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"walls\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"pavements\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"bridges\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1299}, {\"ngram\": \"theEiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1329}, {\"ngram\": \"another way\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1346}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1370}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Put simply: When Olympic visitors flock in their millions to Paris for the July 26-Aug. 11 Games, they will be crowding onto the turf of France's most international, invasive and intriguing contemporary street artist.\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1435, \"end\": 1440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7174758504898245e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1511, \"end\": 1517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999997322147823, \"rank\": 9.826040845359723e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic visitors\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"their millions\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1431}, {\"ngram\": \"-Aug.\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1461}, {\"ngram\": \"the turf\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1507}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be one invasion coming face-to-face with another.\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1649, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one invasion\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"face\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1635}, {\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1648}]}, {\"sentence\": \"LikeBanksy, the British street artist he is sometimes likened to, Invader is elusive, fiercely protective of his anonymity and operating on the margins of illegality.\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999989809157986, \"rank\": 7.403949477563064e-07, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"LikeBanksy\", \"from\": 1651, 